<bug>
    <id>577439</id>
    <title>Part of new Firefox pull-down button visible in full screen mode</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; en-US; rv:2.0b1) Gecko/20100630 Firefox/3.6.3 Erwin
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; en-US; rv:2.0b1) Gecko/20100630 Firefox/3.6.3 Erwin</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When entering full screen mode, there's a small gray bar at the top of the screen - nothing out of the ordenary there.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">However, in FF4.0 beta 1, the new orange Firefox pull-down menu button is visible (and functional) there.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Expected would be to not have this strip there.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 Open Firefox 4.0 beta 1</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 Press F11</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">3 Note a small strip of the orange button persist on the gray bar at the top of the window.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.5">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.6">Orange button present on full screen window.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
No orange button present.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Tested only on FF4.0 beta 1, Windows 7 64bit (tabs on top).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
